ol.li: 35 belong to S. argenteus species (ST2250). The operon is 90% identical to canonical S. aureus agr group 1 operon, however species specific SNPs led to low AgrVATE scores.
Remaining 16 belong to S. aureus species (ST133 and ST59) but have agr operons only 96% identical to canonical agr group 1 operon. For reference other group 1 operons share > 98% identity.
